inn1.comm: goes full and wide of off stump, McCullum leaves, that's a bit of a tight call as it wasn't all that far away
pitches it up again and gets appreciable away movement off the track as McCullum shoulders arms, lots of swing on that ball away from the batsman

loud shot and Lee sets off in celebration but Ian Gould stands unmoved! Lee hits a fullish length and gets the ball to swing in but McCullum gets the thinnest of inside edges as he attempts to work the ball toward midwicket
fuller in length with some good away swing and carry to Paine behind the stumps as McCullum again opts to shoulder arms
full again and still Lee gets movement away from McCullum, who again leaves the ball be

what a ball! Much, much fuller in length, aiming at the yorker on off stump, the ball pitches middle and off and then beats the bat by nothing as McCullum goes to clip the ball and misses, that swung very, very late and somehow missed the edge, lovely bowling that
strays down the pads with a shorter ball, Paine collects
drifts down the pads, 144ks, McCullum again goes for the flick and mistimes it, the ball dribbling off his pads to midwicket as he calls Redmond
bangs his first ball in hard and gets it to sit up, but it's too straight and McCullum hops up to work it toward midwicket with ease
similar ball and again he gets up to knock it to midwicket
too full and he drives fluently into the covers where Hauritz moves well to his left to save runs, he judged the ball and went back and across to stop it
advances and checks the shot, Siddle fumbles, no run though
pitches full and straight, 144ks, gets some movement in and McCullum eases a drive straight to cover
full again and McCullum thuds forward, adjusting to defend the ball back down the track to Siddle who collects
pitches full and Redmond defends ... he's got a high backlift that faces third slip, and keeps shaking the bat as the bowler runs in
cut away as he sees room, its a hurried shot and in the air wide of gully, there's a misfield by Siddle down near third man and Redmond gets a couple
fuller and closer to off stump, deviates off the track and beats Redmond as he feels for it with poor movement, the late movement did him in there
full again, 145ks, Redmond leaves and the ball dies before reaching Paine behind the stumps, stayed a bit low too
full outside off again, 147ks, and Redmond leaves
gets bat on ball now, staying in his crease and defending to point
ah, beaten! Good ball from Siddle again, pitching it up on a teasing length that sucks McCullum forward, then it sits up and deviates past the outer edge as McCullum plays down the wrong line
edged and taken! Siddle takes out McCullum with bounce, bangs it in and gets McCullum flashing outside off stump, there's a thin nick and Paine gobbles it up
good ball again, this one is fuller and cuts back in from outside off stump and Guptill shoulders arms
too straight and Guptill opens his account by tucking the ball off his pads into the gap at midwicket, gets an easy couple
full ball a foot outside off stump, straightens as Guptill leaves
short of a length, 144ks, defended off the back foot
loose defensive shot from Redmond, feet not moving, unsure as to what direction to go and he ends up defending with an inside edge outside off stump
fullish length, starts to swing, Redmond pushes uneasily to cover
pitches middle and leg and deviates, Redmond stays on the back foot and manages to defend the ball to the off side
short ball and it was a matter of time before Lee hurled that down, 150ks, gets Redmond ducking low as the ball deviates at pace and height
beaten on a terrible drive, feet don't move and he flashes at a much fuller ball, which swings away ever so slightly
hits a length on the off-stump line and Redmond defends
pitches it up, 146ks, and Guptill shoulders arms
full again, this time shaping back in from outside off, Guptill defends with soft hands and looks up at Redmond, then they pinch a sharp single
full outside off again, 145ks, Redmond leaves well enough be
first aggressive shot that Redmond connects to, driving at another full ball just outside off, not timed well and the ball rolls toward point
short ball surprises Redmond, who reacts quickly to duck but then tries to sort of waft it down to fine leg, except he doesn't connect
full this time and Redmond wafts and misses
gets forward to a full ball and taps it to cover for a sharp single
flashes at a full ball, losing a hand off the bat handle, feet not moving at all, and the ball gets lodged off the inside edge between his left pad
slower ball, nearly a yorker, swings a bit and Redmond jams it out and gets a single for his efforts because Guptill is alert to call him down
short of a length, too straight, 147ks, defended back
pitches fuller and stays low to beat the bat as he cuts loosely
first four for a while, in fact the first! Lee pitches full and Guptill drives handsomely down past mid-off, good shot that was
bangs it in and gets Redmond hopping back to defend
reaches out and drives a fuller ball straight to Hauritz at cover
a bit of room and Redmond uses the pace and width to pick up a single, steering the ball wide of backward point
pitches much closer to off stump and he defends to point
full from wider of the crease and he defends to the off side again
short of a length and he gets up to tap the ball to point
short of a length on the stumps and he goes back to defend, the ball rolls into the off side and Guptill and Redmond are quick to react
full and wide, just, at 139ks, and easily left alone
leaves him with the angle, 139ks, and he shoulders arms
too straight and he turns the ball to midwicket
shorter ball sits up, 141ks, and gets Redmond rising to defend the ball down in front of backward point
fuller ball, just outside off, sucks him into a drive, there's a noise as he plays the shot, Paine collects and they all go up but umpire Gould shakes his head
back of a length and he defends
fuller ball on middle and leg and he plays a loose drive
goes over cover and point with a full-blooded drive to a full ball
gets room and cuts but straight to Hussey at backward point
bouncer down the leg stump, 145ks, gets him ducking
strays down the pads and he works it off his hips
full on the pads and he defends the ball back
beaten! Hits a length, 141ks143ks, and he defends to the off side
flicks a full ball off his pads to square leg where Hopes misfields
back of a length outside leg and he gets back to defend
again back of a length and this time he opens the face to steer a single, getting  third man into play
pitches it up and Guptill pushes the ball to the off side
veers onto the pads and he clips out to deep backward square
full again, 130ks, and he clips straight to mid-on
hits a length, 134ks, and Redmond goes back to defend, he gets an inside edge that dribbles away to the off and in a flash Guptill calls him down
loose short-arm-jab, ball stays low and takes an under edge that falls short of Paine, who is beaten by the poor bounce as well
flashes and flashes well, hitting a wider ball into the gap between cover and point for a four, that is well struck
full and wide, 139ks, Guptill leaves and wide not called
back of a length and he punches nicely toward extra cover
gets up on the toes and pushes the ball to backward point
swing back in this time, pitches full, 128ks, he hurries to get bat and pad together and pushes the ball to the off side
overpitches this time and Guptill square-drives into the gap for one
full and straight and he pushes tightly to extra cover and harries off, the fielder is a bit late and Redmond makes it home in time
makes room and hammers a full ball in the air to mid-off, it drops just short of Lee there
turns this one off the pads and gets a single
hits a length and Redmond defends off the back foot
gets back and runs the ball down wide of backward point
comes firmly onto the front foot and defends a fullish ball to cover
drives a length ball hard square on the off side, just into the gap

pitches full and wide, 142ks, he chases it in the air and the ball just skims the outstretched fingertips of Hussey at backward point, that was hit hard and the ball flew to Hussey, who leaped up goalie style and nearly managed to hold on ... it would be harsh to call that a drop
comes onto the front foot and defends
shuffles across to glance it fine and gets struck on the pads
shot! Johnson errs in length, overpitching just outside off stump, and Gutpill hammers a very straight off drive that beats a diving mid-off
too wide, slips out of the hand and Paine has to collect it
another forceful off drive to a full ball, leans into the half volley and hits it straight, mid-off dives and gets a hand to it but it ricochets away from Ferguson for four
smart batting from Guptill, running a single down to third man to end the over and keep strike ... New Zealand post their fifty as well
back of a length on the off, drops it down towards point, thinks of a single but decides against it wisely
bangs it in short, down the leg side too, Guptill backs away from it and Dar stretches his arms
bowled on a good length on middle, pushes it gently down to mid-on

a bit of confusion out in the middle, darted back in a hint, chopped it down just wide of the stumps, wasn't too sure it that was heading back onto the wickets, hesitated to take the single but did so comfortably in the end, an attempt at a direct hit at the bowler's end, misses, and concedes an overthrow
bowled fullish on middle, driven through the line to mid-on
banged in short outside off, a harmless bouncer, left alone to the keeper
bowled full on the off, pushed down towards mid-off
worked away to midwicket off the front foot
quickish on the off, pushed through the line to the bowler
bowled it on a length on middle and leg, chipped down towards long-on for a single to bring up the 50-stand
trying to be attacking, full outside off, and bowled quick too, made room and tried to smack him hard over mid-off, didn't get hold of it but still managed to steal two
pushed it through to mid-off for a quick single
banged in short outside off, ducked under it and tried to upper cut it over the keeper, didn't connect but earned a wide nevertheless
fullish on the off stump, swung hard at it and mistimed it to midwicket
banged in short outside off, tried to knock it down towards third man but it kept low and zipped under him
the legcutter bowled full on the off, there to smack and Redmond obliges, dashing it over mid-on for a boundary

continues to be a little scratchy here,full outside off, makes plenty of room and then struggles to reach it as he tries to steer it past point, doesn't make contact, the ball just escaped the off stump
back of a length, close to the off stump, chopped down to third man for a single
pitched up on middle, presents the full face as he drives it to long-on, nicely timed but just for a single
shortish on middle, punched back to the bowler
full on middle and leg, driven down to long-on, well timed again

stumped, Redmond's not had a good day, came down the track and Hauritz spotted him, hurled it wide and Redmond had a wild swing at it, couldn't reach it and Paine clipped off the bails to find him short
quickish and turning in from outside off, pushed it back to the bowler off the back foot
much slower through the air this time, flighted it outside off, had to reach for it as he played it into the leg side
tossed up and full outside off, pushes it gently back to the bowler
short of a good length on the off, nudges it down into the leg side for an easy single
confidently played, full and wide, leant into the drive and played it straight to sweeper cover for a single
bowled on a good length outside off, guides it with an open face down to point
shortish on leg stump, just whipped through midwicket for a couple of runs
hitting the pitch hard, rocks back and drops it down onto the pitch, the non-striker calls for a single and the batsman, with a slight hint of hesitation, eventually responds to complete it in time
short of a good length outside off, darted back in just a hint and he shouldered arms to it
good length outside off, placed wide of point for a single
pushed through to cover point for a single
bowled full on the off, driven down to long-on for a single
went straight on and beat the batsman, tossed it up outside off and Guptill was playing for the turn as he tried to nudge it down towards point, missed as it didn't turn
threw it up outside off, taken on the full and driven back to the bowler
deceived by the turn this time, kept a little low too, Guptill played at it, missed and it just escaped the off stump
worked away off the back foot into the leg side for a single
short of a length outside off, reaches for it and knocks it down to third man for a single
shortish outside off, angling in a touch, plays at it with soft hands, gets an edge and it lands short of slip
some extra bounce this time, angling in and then moving away off the pitch, Taylor fishes at it and is beaten
bowled it fullish on the off, at 141.9 kmph, sliced it uppishly wide of point for a single
edged and short, for the second time in the over, bowled full and gets a hint of away movement, thick outside edge but doesn't carry
bowled it on a good length on middle, shuffles a hint and sweeps it down to long leg for a single
caught and bowled, straightforward delivery that, bowled full and flat outside off, Guptill pushed at it firmly and scooped an easy catch back to the bowler
flighted and full outside off, tickled wide of midwicket for a single
turning in from a good length on middle, turned down wide of short fine
threw it up outside off, driven elegantly wide of deep cover for a couple of runs
turning in sharply but still not as much as Elliott expects it to, tries to open the face to that one but is beaten

gone! Bowled it on a good length outside off, gets to the pitch to drive it past point but ends up slicing it just wide of him, Hussey flings himself to his right and takes it over his head, excellent effort
bowled full outside off, a touch too wide there and it's left alone
fullish outside off, gets forward and guides it down to point
hurls in in towards middle and off and 143.6 kmph, pushed down to mid-off
short of a good length outside off and maintains its line, left alone to the keeper

poor stuff, full outside off, guided it wide of point, Hussey dive to his left to field that well but then threw it at the wrong end, aimed at the stumps at the keeper's end, missed and conceded overthrows, costly ones too
appeal for lbw, yorker, just outside of, raps the batsman on his toes, big appeal from Lee and it's rightly turned down, struck him outside the line

swinging in, bowled full outside off, tries to drive it through the line back past the bowler but he's a little late on the shot, gets a thick outside edge through where second slip would normally be and earns four
pitched up on the off stump, pushed down to cover on the front foot
hurling it full just outside off, bowled at 147.2 kmph, defended just wide of the bowler
bangs it in short this time, good pace, 148.4 kmph, Broom ducks under it easily
short of a good length outside off, tapped down off the back foot towards point
full on the off, driven uppishly through to deep cover for one more
bowls it on a good length outside off, defended solidly down to cover
sliding it down on the pads this time, tries to work it fine, is struck high on the pads and they steal a single wide of midwicket
lands on a good length outside off, gets across to play it down to point
back of a length on the off, run down to point
short one outside off, held its line, left alone to the keeper
got it fuller this time, just a fraction outside off, defended down to point
bouncer, down the leg side through, misdirected, given a wide, Lee isn't happy but he shouldn't be happy with himself for bowling it there
dragged it short on middle, gets back and drops it wide of midwicket for a single

trapped in front, the inswinging yorker gets him a wicket, Elliott was too late trying to defend it into the off side, it struck him hard on the pads right in front of middle, the umpire had no hesitation, went back to play at it and was caught plumb in front, too quick
short of a good length on the off, pushed towards cover
Franklin's lucky, hurled it short outside off, he just hangs his bat out, gets a thick edge to beat third man as he tries to cut it off
angling it in towards middle, worked away through square leg for a single
swinging in this time, pitched on middle, gets front and across and turns it down to midwicket
excellent shot, positive stuff from Broom , was in the slot bowled full outside off, got to the pitch and drove it stylishly through extra cover and mid-off to bring up the 100
the inswinger again, fullish on the off stump, defended with a still head to extra cover
pitched up outside off, drives it hard and firm but straight to Cameron White at extra cover
swinging in, lands on a length outside off, gets forward and blocks it confidently
banged in short just outside off, struggles to keep it down, plays it uppishly down to third man through gully
short one again, the attempted bouncer, just outside off, Broom backs away from it
slower one this time, bowled at 122 kmph, fullish outside off, defended towards cover
another bouncer-wide down the leg side, seen a few of those from Lee
going for the inswinging yorker, fullish on middle, driven nicely down to deep midwicket for a single
hurling it hard on leg stump at 149.3 kmph, pushed through to midwicket off the back foot
lands on a good length outside off, just a hint of away movement there, left alone
shortish outside off, chops it wide of point down to third man for a single
lands on a good length outside off, pushing it past the bowler down to mid-off
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the back foot to cover
pitched up on a driving length outside off, drives it uppishly past point for a single
full on the off stump, Broom gets forward and defends it rock solid to extra cover
angling in on middle, turned away to midwicket
flighted into the rough from around the stumps and Franklin uses the room to steer the ball wide of slip and gully, turning the face of the bat, to pick up four
fuller, straighter delivery which he defends soundly to the off
shuffles across and turns the ball to the leg side
again Broom goes back and across and works the ball to midwicket
tosses it up outside off and Broom goes back to defend
gives this ball some flight and Broom stretches forward to defend
gets back and tucks a length ball to the on side
fuller ball angles into middle and leg and Franklin defends
full outside off and he squirts it to Hussey at backward point
back of a length outside off, angles in and Franklin pushes to point
fuller, nips back in and Franklin plods forward
holds back the length and he steers it down wide of point
flights it into the pads and he turns the ball to midwicket
well kept, the ball spins down Broom's pads, he misses, and Paine collects swiftly and breaks the sticks but all is well
goes for a sweep to one tossed up outside off and gets a top edge over Paine that drops safely in no mans land
on-drives a fuller and flatter ball toward mid-on
tosses it up just outside off and Broom square-drives a single
slower ball on a length, Franklin stabs at it and knocks it back
drifts back in and Franklin, on the front foot, runs it to point
full outside off and he opens the face to manufacture a single
pitches it on a length and beats a loose drive, lacking footwork
leans into a fuller ball and drives hard but right to Ponting at short cover, who lets the ball out in a flash but misses the stumps at the other end, nobody is backing up and Franklin gets a single
full on middle and leg and Broom on-drives the ball
drives an overpitched delivery to extra cover
gets another full ball and square-drives past point for one more
tossed up on the pads and he turns the ball to the fielder
uses his feet and drives well past extra cover for a couple
better length and some turn draws a leading edge to the off side
steps out and Hauritz changes the pace, pitching it fuller and wider too and Broom gets an edge that rolls down past where slip could have been
uses his feet to take it on the full and picks up one to mid-on
flat on the leg stump, Franklin clips the ball past Hauritz
pitches full, Franklin drives to Ponting at short cover, he again releases the ball in a flash and hits something, not the stumps, and the ball ricochets for a single
slower ball, Broom is early into the stroke and rolls to mid-on
cuts a wide ball but cannot beat Hussey at backward point
pitches it up and Broom defends to Hussey this time

ouch, that one spits up from a length, takes the inner edge and hits Broom where it hurts, Siddle just turns on his mark, shaking his head, and marches back, no mercy from the big man who is clearly down with something
back of a length and Broom defends it back
tossed up from around the stumps, Franklin comes forward and stabs at the ball as it turns in and it runs off the flap of his pads
dabs a wider ball to the man at backward point
holds back the length to bring Franklin reaching out and driving to cover
gets a big stride forward and gets struck just outside the line
dances out and chips the ball over Hauritz, it drops in front of long-on
good ball, gets some turn but more importantly bounce, to lure him forward and then in no mans land, edging safely through where a slip needs to be plugged
positive shot from Broom, driving a fullish ball to Ponting at short cover
gets over a shorter ball and cuts it into the ground in front of Ponting
pushes a full ball on off stump back to Siddle
short ball down the leg side gets Broom up on one leg, swatting it away
change of pace and length, pitches it outside leg stump and gets some lift, Franklin pushes the ball in the air wide of Siddle and in front of extra cover
leans into a full ball and finds the gap in the covers
pitches it up and Broom drives well to extra cover
gets room and opens the face to steer a single to third man
back of a length, angles in and he taps the ball to cover
full outside off and driven wide of extra cover but no run there
slower one there, Franklin drives to the off and sets off, White collects from midwicket and flings the ball, just misses the stumps and Ian Gould too!
comes dancing out and flashes at the ball, slicing it over gully for four
strays outside leg stump and Franklin turns it away off his pads, superbly through square leg as well for back-to-back fours to the total
short outside off and he steers the ball wide of point and that pleasing shot raises the 50-run stand
smart batting, just comes onto the front foot and pushes the fuller ball to mid-off for a single
starts to walk out but Siddle holds back the length, so Broom just defends with soft hands and urges Franklin on
beaten on a loose push outside off, Siddle bends his back and gets good bounce off the deck, well bowled there
top shot to a full ball, drives hard, drives straight, and drives for four
they're stepping it up now, full outside off and he crashes it hard over mid-on for a boundary to bring up his highest score in ODIs
bowled on a good length outside off, tries to nudge it down to third man but doesn't connect
short and wide, chopped down straight to point
four more, pitched up outside off, charges down the track and rams it over mid-off for four more

run out off an atrocious delivery, high full toss outside off, played it down to point, Franklin wanted a single but Broom hesitated, he was running back to his end and then turned back, was too late to respond to Franklin's call and Hussey at point returned a safe throw down to Watson who took off the bails to find Broom miles short
bowled full on the pads, tried to glance it fine, didn't middle it, gets an inside edge onto his pads and a single to keep the strike
short of a good length on the off, chopped down to point off the back foot
short of a good length on the off, drops it short of Lee and steals a quick single
well played, short outside off, there's a slip in place but he took the risk, upper-cut Lee over the keeper and slip for a boundary
inside edge, full outside off, tried to drive it through the covers but it went to fine leg instead
hurling it on a good length on middle and leg, pushed down towards mid-on
the yorker, straight on off stump at 146 kmph, Franklin made room to dig that out into the off side bu the bat came down too late and the stump went on a walk
shortish outside off, cut down to deep point for a single
pitched up outside off, went for the drive but he got some movement off the pitch to beat the outside edge
fullish on the off, textbook stuff from Butler as he pushes it back to the bowler
probing line outside off, pushed through to cover off the front foot
slower one bowled full outside off, chips it down towards wide long-off for a couple
good stuff, short of a good length outside off, came across and pulled it powerfully over midwicket for a one bounce four
bowled flat, on a good length on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
held back his length there, short and turning in, played to extra cover
threw it up outside off, reached forward and defended it cautiously towards cover

he's given him! Tossed it up outside off and it turned in, Butler came forward and tried to play it across the line towards square leg, missed and was rapped on the pads. It would have gone on, but we need a replay to check whether or not he was struck outside the line, looked out on first sight
tossed up on the off stump, worked away to midwicket
short on the off stump, turned off the back foot behind square for a single
short of a good length outside off, pushed down towards point
missed run-out, pushed off the back foot wide of Hussey for a single, a direct throw at the bowler's head would have had him
blocked off the back foot in front of Hussey for a single, a direct hit this time but he's well in
slowish at 128.3 kmph, gets forward and guides it down to point again
lands on a driving length on the off stump, defended down to extra cover
full and wide, drives at it from the crease, missed it, so did the otherwise impressive Paine behind the stumps, concedes a bye
tossed it up outside off, taken on the full and pushed it to extra cover
full on the off, driven down to long-off for a single
the slog-sweep, straight to deep midwicket for a single
another one, straight to deep square leg this time, flighted outside off and he went for it
slowed it up, tossed up, defended wide of midwicket for one run
threw it up just outside off, dropped in front of midwicket to steal a single
bowled full on the off, driven off the front foot to mid-off
slower one dragged in short on middle, fends it away wide behind square for a single

a possible injury, full outside off, pushed it wide of extra cover and got the single, they attempt a second as the diving Ponting deflects it in front of Ferguson at mid-off, he runs in to gather it and prevent them from taking the second, twists his right ankle as he bends to collect and then tumbles. He's in some pain there, and the physio's out
run-out, that's gone, dropped down in front of Ponting who runs, collects and throws down the stumps in one motion at the striker's end to send Mills back to the pavilion
hurling it fast on full on middle from round the wicket, played back to the bowler
beat the outside off, just full outside off, tries to angle it down to third man, doesn't connect
bowled full on middle, makes room to drive it back to the bowler, Lee tries to stop it on his follow through but can't save the single
appeared to be a harsh call from Dar there, called that snorter a wide, just evaded Bond's helmet as he tried to move away
full on the off, guided down to point
banged in short outside off, another attempted bouncer, tried to play at it but it was too quick
fullish on middle, tries to close the face to work it past midwicket for a single
full, fast and wide, makes room to steer it past point, misses

dropped, bowled on a good length on middle and off, Patel made room and tried to open the face, got a thick edge and Paine, who had moved to his left, had to cover some ground while diving to his right to pluck that one, a hard low catch and he couldn't get his gloves down in time
short of a length outside off, cut down straight to Hussey at point
slowed it down, full outside off, tried to clear long-off but didn't time it well enough, just a single for all that effort
in the slot on middle, tries to swing it over midwicket but again mistimed, straight to Ponting
short and wide, goes for the cut, misses, had to reach for it
bowled full on the off, smacked down to Johnson at long-off for one more
short of a length outside off, makes room to play it through the covers, nothing comes off it, rolls down to the keeper
low full toss outside off, slaps it down to long-on for a single
length ball outside off, makes room to swing it hard over long-on, gets a thick inside edge behind square for a single
made room and he hurled it short, bowled at 144.7 kmph, Patel chose to back away, and lost his balance to crash into the ground
bowled it full this time, low full toss on middle, pushed back to the bowler
bouncer, hurled it short on middle, Patel ducked under it easily, no way they're going to get 200 playing like this
well, goes for one finally, short and wide and he cuts it over point to reach 200

inn2.comm: nervy start for Watson! Just swings away late and the batsman gets an inside edge which rolls away, McCullum charges towards the ball and takes aim at the other end
gets a bit of late swing again and Paine pushes it to mid-on
gets well forward to cover the movement and pushes it to the covers
two slips in place, gentle swing away and confidently defended to the covers
gets forward to cover the movement and a defensive push is enough to beat point, Bond is square at third man
gives it a mighty whack but he finds Patel at square leg
late inswing for Bond, lands on a fullish length outside off and he pushes it to cover

Bond strikes straightaway! Lovely catch by Taylor to back him up, he swings it away from the right-hander and pitches it up on the correct spot and lures him to go for the drive, Taylor snaps the outside edge diving low to his right
he loses his direction and sprays it wide of the off stump, left alone by Ponting
gets a very confident stride forward and drives just wide of mid-off
charges in and fires it in full on the pads and he just manages to tickle it away, works up some swing there
targets the line just outside off and Ponting shuffles across and taps it away to the off side
hits a nice length just outside off and there's good bounce and carry to the keeper
tucks it away close to his pads and Mills appeals half heartedly

now Mills joins the party, Ponting's all at sea with this one, the ball lands on the off stump line and nips back in, Ponting shuffles across only slightly but he's too late in covering the line, trapped right in front of middle, no issues with height, Mills knows it, he turns back for confirmation and Ponting has to go
White gets a lifter straightaway but he manages to fend it off with soft hands
lands it on middle and off and he gets across and taps it to the on side
keeps it on the off stump line and there's gentle away movement before reaching the keeper
just a trifle wide outside the off stump and left alone
87.4 mph, fires it outside the off stump and the batsman gets right across his stumps and decides to shoulder arms
keeps it on the same line and length, the batsman is happy to let this one go as well
88.4 mph, gets the outside edge this time but safe of any fielder, third man picks it up
swings it in late honing in on the off stump, he gets forward and gets some wood on that as he pushes it to the off side
White gets a 89.9 mph snorter from Bond which he just about manages to fend away with soft hands, well played by White
gets beside the line and taps it away to the off side

Watson breaks free and Australia will be relieved, Mills bangs it in short and we all know how strong Watson is on the leg side, the fine leg is up and he places it well wide of him and gets a boundary to long leg
gets a bit of width to cut and he chops it to the off side
lands it on a good length outside off and he safely shoulders arms
slices him in half and Watson pauses for a few seconds, the ball moves back in from outside off and nearly takes the inside edge onto the stumps
lands it on a fuller length and he pushes it away to mid-on
88 mph, teasing line outside the off stump, the ball holds its line and nearly takes the outside edge on the drive
88.7 mph, this is intense stuff folks, lands on the corridor of uncertainty outside off, kicks up and nearly shaves the face of the bat, McCullum nearly goes up in appeal
swings it in late and he pushes it away to the on side for a couple, low full toss actually
88.9 mph, gets bounce off a good length and White shoulders arms
this time White gets across and fends it off down the pitch
streaky! But a very tough one for second slip, White chases a delivery pitched up and wide of the off stump, the thick outside edge just beats second slip who flings himself to his right
defended back to the bowler
pitched on middle and ,leg, appeals for a lbw but it was missing leg
pushes it to the off side
lands it on a good length outside off and he pushes it away towards slip
stays back and pushes it down to mid-on
gentle medium pace outside the off stump and he safely lets it go to the keeper
stays beside the line and punches it down to point
88.2 mph, swings it in late on the off stump and he gets well forward and pushes it to cover
89.7mph, he delivers from wide of the crease to generate more inswing and he nearly induces an outside edge on the off drive, well bowled
88.2 mph, gets it to kick up off a good length, he drops his wrists and fends it off well
switches to a fuller length and he drives it down towards mid-off
gets a lot of inswing this time and White does really well to not offer a shot
pitches it just outside off and he softly taps it to the off side
lands it just outside off and he angles it wide of point
82.7 mph, wide outside off and at a gentle pace, he should have spanked that
in the slot to drive past mid-on but he pushes it straight to the fielder
bowls it on the corridor just outside the off stump and White gets across and lets it go
stays beside the line and chops it to cover, cramps him for room to force it through
85.1 mph, catches the batsman in a moment of circumspection, rises up alarmingly off a good length and the batsman pokes his bat out and then withdraws the glove
stays behind the line and taps it to the on side
another beautiful delivery, he lunges forward to defend and the ball swings back in and nearly shaves the edge
walks across the stumps and taps it to the offside
gets right across his stumps and defends off the full face of the bat
fullish in length outside off and he drives firmly to mid-off
teasing line on the off stump, equally well played there as he gets a decent stride across and defends
lands it just outside off, he gets across and defends to the off side
delivers from wide of the crease and hones it in on middle and off, defended to the off side
continues from wide of the crease, holds the length back outside off, he gets back and across and defends
close! He plays all around an inswinger on the stumps and manages an inside edge onto the pads, they appeal and realise he's safe
finally gets a run away, knocks it on the gap between midwicket and mid-on
nearly gets a wicket! Lovely delivery which hones in just outside the off stump, holds its line and nearly takes the edge
lands it on middle and off and he gets some wood behind it this time
keeps it just outside off and he steers it to the off side
gets a bit of width outside off and he punches it hard but finds backward point
nice square cut to break the spell, gets a bit of width outside off, he goes back and across, rolls his wrists and slaps it past backward point and cover

big appeal for a caught behind, he leans forward for the drive and the ball kicks up and nearly takes the edge, the batsman looks back, McCullum was up immediately  but the umpire shakes his head, I need to see the snicko on that
opens the face and deftly angles it down to third man
delivers from wide of the crease, defended back to the bowler
stays back and punches it with the movement to midwicket
shoulders arms outside off
keeps it dead straight outside off and the batsman covers the line and defends
keeps him quiet again, cramps him for room and the batsman pushes it to the off side
lands it on a good length just outside off, not much swing, defended to the off side
holds the length back slightly but played to the same area, the two slips are wide of each other
good slower ball, has the batsman lunging forward, softly tapped to the off side
shuffles and clips it away to short midwicket
stays right behind the line and defends down the track
comes beside the line and pushes it wide of cover point
pitches outside leg and that one is nudged off the pads for one
poor line, well outside leg stump and Watson gets a faint tickle on that which sends the ball away for four to fine leg
short of a length on middle and leg and he defends it back
overpitched, 123ks, and Watson leans into a good-looking drive to Redmond at extra cover who saves runs
gets nice and tall and punches the ball past White, sets off, and makes it home even as mid-off returns a close throw that narrowly misses a bail
hops up and turns the ball off his hips for a couple
gets up and punches the ball back and Butler sticks out a hand
drags it down and Watson tries to pull but the ball skids on at a much lower height than anticipated and he takes it near the midriff, then the ball rolls fine
fuller ball, Watson gets into it nicely with an on-drive
ah, that was mistimed and over mid-on! Watson pulls but takes it high off the bat, somehow manages to clear Bond rather easily in the end
short in length and he swivels to pull down to deep square leg
full outside off stump and White leaves it be for McCullum
comes forward and pushes the ball to backward point
pitches on middle and leg and he defends it back
short of a length, angling in from just outside leg stump, and Watson goes back and uses the wrists to work the ball behind square leg for four, excellent shot that
fuller ball, 120ks, and Watson pushes it back firmly
goes back again to a short ball and works it to midwicket
short of a length again and Watson is right in line defending
hits a full length and White thuds forward in defense
gets some room outside off and goes hard at the ball, with too much bottom hand and not enough movement of the feet, and chops the ball to Guptill at cover

dropped! White goes to pull a shorter ball and makes a meal of it, all wrong with the balance, and the ball flies up off the shoulder of the bat very, very high to the leg side, McCullum runs across to his left but fails to catch it, it was hard because it was spiraling but he needed to pouch that
gets forward and defends to point
sweet! Leans into a fullish ball and beats extra cover, awesome shot
straighter ball, which he turns to square leg
flat ball from over the stumps, too straight and turned to midwicket
a bit too wide and that is an amazing shot, just leaned back and opened the face, using the pace of the quicker ball to pick up four past gully
pushes it in flatter and Watson drives it back off the back foot
spins down the pads, Watson shuffles and nudges around the corner
smears this one across the line, beating a diving midwicket, and Franklin does well in the deep, covering plenty of ground and sliding just in front of the ropes
tossed up outside off, he goes for a late dab and gets beaten
good shot, just goes back and punches the ball off the back foot past a diving cover and gets the cover sweeper into play, he's coming along slowly is White
pulls a shortish ball and miscues it, hitting it into the ground
too short and he pulls behind square, out in the deep the sweeper dives, and that is the 50-run stand up
leans into a full ball and drives excellently to a sliding Elliott at mid-off
back of a length and he stands up to punch it back to Butler
straighter ball squares him up but the ball rolls safely to point
tosses it up and that one is pushed off the back foot to midwicket
flatter, fuller ball on middle and leg and he pats it back
slows it up and drifts it wide, White makes room and slashes but cannot connect
slower, with some loop on it, dips on the pads and he turns it for one
drags back the length and he works it past square leg for one
touch too short, spins in and Watson punches it past point
stands upright and steers the wide ball behind point for one more
pitches on a length and stays a wee bit low, defended off the back foot
take that! That is a flat six, just picked up the length and slammed it over midwicket with some power, what a shot
pitches on a fuller length just outside off and Watson defends
fuller and wider and he steers it down to third man for one
fuller in length and he defends it to the off side
tossed up on middle and off and he patiently pats it back
fuller and flatter and he flicks past midwicket for two
change of pace, much slower, pitches off and Watson defends
this is one-way traffic now! Watson reaches out and collects the ball with power, dumping it over deep midwicket for half a dozen
now he gets cheeky, opening the face to try and steer a single but gets beaten
again he goes back to manufacture a run, gets beaten, McCullum collects and breaks the sticks
starts off full outside off and White leaves that one be
back of a length and he watchfully defends to the off side
short and that is pulled past midwicket superbly, just spotted the error in length, rolled the wrists, picked the gap, and got four
beaten this time, sees a shortish ball and slogs and misses
change of pace, 123ks, hits a yorker length well outside off stump and beats a drive from White
smartly played, drops the wrists and runs the ball past Taylor at slip
fullish length on the pads and he turns it to midwicket
too straight again and this one is worked around the corner for one
good ball, searches for the yorker and nearly pulls it off but Watson pushes it down the ground for a single
now that is poor, slides down the pads and White glances for four
full and straight and White defends
full and straight again, White drives it back, Elliott sticks out a hand but cannot get there, the ball hits the stumps
short of a good length outside off, chopped down to point
slightly short outside off, pushed off the back foot wide of extra cover to reach his half-century, an innings under pressure
back of a length on middle, defended respectfully back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, stands tall and pushes it down to extra cover
another short one, just a fraction outside off, he had his eye on the stands behind square leg there, went for a fierce pull but missed
targeting the blockhole outside off, ends up full, steered down to deep point for a single
bowled full outside off, leans into the drive and plays it on the bounce to the extra-cover fielder who fumbles, the crowd thinks he's dropped a catch
gets it to land on a good length on the off stump, reaches forward and plays it back
bowling it full on middle, drives it straight down to mid-on
targeting a good length on the off, worked into the leg side behind square for a single
fullish outside off, driven straight to extra cover
short outside off, a bit of extra bounce there for Franklin, Watson tries to cut that down towards third man but is a little surprised as it shot up
bowls it on a length and fast outside off, driven through to extra cover
nicely timed, overpitched and there to be hit, White bends low and just pushes it hard past the bowler and mid-off for four runs
unlucky, that was a good bouncer, White goes for the hook, he gets the top edge and over the keeper for four more, that was all effort from Bond but the result would have hurt
steams in and hurls it full on the off stump, defended watchfully back to Bond
short outside off, cutting in just a touch, tries to work it behind point, gets an inside edge and lands wide of the stumps
the offcutter bowled from wide of the crease, angling in, defended with a straight bat back to the bowler

big appeal for lbw, coming round the wicket, angling in towards middle, Watson tried to defend it on the front foot with a straight bat, missed and was struck on the pads, a really close shout that, struck just in line and would have clipped the bails, say the replays. Could have gone either way
worked away into the leg side through midwicket for a single
fullish on middle and leg, clipped off the pads to deep midwicket for a single to bring up the 100
pitched it on a good length on the off, gets forward, closes the face and drives it to mid-on
short of a good length on the off, drops it off the back foot in front of midwicket for a single
powerfully struck, fraction short outside off and Watson is onto it, gets into position and pulls it disdainfully through midwicket for a boundary
full on the off, driven straight to extra cover
gets to his half-century in style, pitched up on the off stump, picks it beautifully, launching it over the bowler's head for a straight six
short of a good length outside off, left alone to the keeper
poor length, too short and he's lucky not to be dispatched, plays it straight to deep midwicket for a single
bowled it on a good length on middle, driven down to mid-on
brilliantly fielded by Broom at point, short and wide and cut really hard, Broom pulls off a superb one-handed save diving to his right, saved a certain boundary there
bowled it full on the off stump, went for a booming drive there, mistimed it to mid-off
short on middle, pulled down to fine leg for a single
full on the off stump, dug out gently in front of mid-off for a quick single
short of a good length outside off, run down to third man for a single
in the blockhole outside off, dug out towards cover from the crease
full and wide, driven hard but straight to extra cover
poor start, short and wide, makes room to cut it hard through point for a boundary
tossed it up and bowled it full on middle, pushed down to midwicket, a slight fumble by Ross Taylor and they get a single
short on middle and leg, tries to whip it down fine, is struck on the thighs
shortish outside off, dabbed from the crease down to point
held back the length slightly, fends it off wide of fine leg for a couple of runs
threw it hard and quick on middle, pulled down to fine leg for a single
banged in short on the off, pushed away off the back foot for one more wide of midwicket, easily done
back of a length outside off, pushed between cover and point for a single
full toss on middle, pushes it gently back to the bowler
angling it in towards off, Watson gets to the pitch and plays a standard defense to cover
fullish outside off, driven down to long-off for a single
bowled it full on the off again, same result, long-off gets into the action
quicker through the air, bowled full on middle, turned down to midwicket
short on middle, punched off the back foot towards the bowler
pushes it wide of Patel this time who can't prevent the single despite his diving attempt
gets on the back foot and plays it down to midwicket
floating it full outside off, gets across and dabs it down to midwicket
fullish on middle and leg, pushed into the gap between square leg and midwicket for a single
back of a length on the off, gets back and blocks it down to point
punished, mid-off is not in his conventional position, has been brought forward, it was full and wide, Watson leaned forward and drove it through the line to beat him comfortably to the ropes
short of a good length on middle, works it away wristily wide of midwicket for a single

bowled'im! Slowish, bowled at 128.3 kmph,  on a good length just outside off, White opted to leave it but really late, got an inside edge just as he was shouldering arms and the off stump was knocked back
slightly short on the off, defended down towards extra cover
bowled full on the off, driven with a straight bat down to mid-off
short on middle and off, rocked back to pull it wide of Mills at deep square leg for a couple of runs
short of a good length outside off, taps it down to third man for a single
shortish on the off stump, drops it down confidently short of extra cover
back of a length on the off, knocks it down, standing tall and rocking back
Hussey's totally unflustered, what a way to start off, short and wide and he latched onto it, hammered it hard over midwicket for a boundary
bowled full on the off, driven through to mid-off with a reach
hurling it straight on middle, driven away down to deep midwicket for a single
three more, tickled through square leg, Redmond chases it but can't gather it on the first attempt in the deep, concedes an extra run
poor stuff, short ball, giving Watson the opportunity to play his favourite shot, all along the ground through midwicket to beat the diving fielder in the deep for a boundary
pushes it full on middle, driven straight to mid-on
another short delivery, Watson doesn't cash in this time but has enough on it to get a couple wide of deep midwicket
bowled full on the off stump, driven past the bowler and the diving mid-off for a couple more
targeting middle, Hussey drives it down to deep midwicket for a single
pitched up outside off, steers it down to point who dives and deflects it off to cover
the slower yorker outside off, Watson was deceived, he couldn't bring his bat down in time
back of a length on the off, defended down towards cover
full on middle and off, dug out back to the bowler
tries to dab it into the off side, gets an inside edge just wide of the stumps down to fine leg for one more
back of a length outside off, runs it down to third man for a single
Mills gets Hussey! Bowled it on a driving length outside off, Hussey is not totally committed to that shot, just scoops that drive straight to Patel at point
shot up from a good length on the off, takes his bottom hand off as he tries to knock it down on the leg side
short outside off, cuts it uppishly, short of Redmond at point
full on the off, driven hard but straight back to Mills who fields it well on his follow through
moved back in off the pitch, Watson let it go but he didn't expect the movement there
poor ball to follow that up and Watson takes full toll, cutting it fiercely through point for a boundary
short of a length outside off, guides it down to third man for one more
back of a length, came back in, kept a little low, Hopes tried to drive it off the back foot through mid-off, missed it
shot, back of a length, Hopes gets back and forces it through that gap between extra cover and mid-off for a boundary
testing line outside off, in the channel, left alone to the keeper
full outside off, driven handsomely but straight to extra cover
bangs it in on middle, peanuts for Watson who swivels and plays  it to fine leg
slower full toss on the off stump, driven straight to mid-on
shortish on the off, rocks back and defends it cautiously back to the bowler
hurls it full on the off, driven just wide of mid-on to complete a single
back of a length, nudges it wide of the keeper, Hopes is interested in the single but Watson sends him back
short of a good length on middle, whipped away through midwicket for a single
banged in short on middle, pulled down to deep square leg where Bond stretches to his left to pull off a good running stop
shortish outside off, goes for the cut, gets a thick outside edge down to third man
jabs it behind point off the back foot to complete 2000 runs in ODI cricket, well done
Hopes is unforgiving on that short one, gets forward and dispatches that poor thing over midwicket for four runs
will feel he missed out there, full outside off, tries to blaze it through the covers, the bat turns in his hand and he mistimes it back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, guides it down to third man
he's finishing this off quickly now, Hopes is showing off his batting skills much at the possible expense of Watson's looming century, drives it hard through the covers and it races to the ropes
lands on a good length on the off, pushed through firmly to mid-off
shortish on middle and leg, turns it down to fine leg for a single
pitched it up outside off, drives it elegantly down to cover
bowled it full on middle, driven down to mid-on
shortish outside off, punched down to extra cover
smeared him with a quick one, full on the off, tried to play it away into the leg side, got an inside edge onto his pads
a touch short on the off stump, pushed down to midwicket
drags it too short and Watson thwacks that through midwicket, we've seen this happen too many times
hurls it full on middle, wisely takes a single to long-on
threw it up on a good length on the off, turns in a hint, pushes it back to Patel
shortish outside off, runs it down to third man for a single
Watson stands a chance of being stranded in the 90s now, short and wide, pulls it away with utter disdain through midwicket
fuller outside off, pushed wide of midwicket for a quick single
short outside off, runs it down to third man and takes the single
slower one bowled fullish on the off, chipped in front of mid-on
full on the off, driven hard but back to the bowler
gets to 99 with a slog-swept six, full outside off and he dismisses that over deep midwicket
finishes it off handsomely and reaches his century in the process, tossed up, full and it meets the same fate, launched into the stands over wide long-on
